info.title: I Don't Know How To Love Him

lines.text: i don't know how to love him,
what to do,-how to move him.
in these-past few days, when i've seen myself,
i don't know how to take this.
i don't see why he moves me.
he's a man, he's just a man.
and i've had so many men-before.
don't you think it's rather funy,
i should be in this position.
i'm the one who's always been
so calm, so cool, no lover's fool,
yet, if he said he loved me,
i'd be lost, i'd be frightened.
i'd turn my head,-i'd back away.

paragraphs.text: i don't know how to love him, what to do,-how to move him. i've been-changed, yes, really changed. in these-past few days, when i've seen myself, i seem like someone else. i don't know how to take this. i don't see why he moves me. he's a man, he's just a man. and i've had so many men-before. in very many ways, he's just one more. should i bring him down? should i scream and shout? should i speak of love, let my feelings out? i never thought i'd come to this. what's it all about? don't you think it's rather funy, i should be in this position. i'm the one who's always been so calm, so cool, no lover's fool, running evry show. he scares me so. i never thought i'd come to this. what's it all about? yet, if he said he loved me, i'd be lost, i'd be frightened. i couldn't cope,-just couldn't cope. i'd turn my head,-i'd back away. i wouldn't want to know. he scares me so. i want him so. i love him so.
